Entrepreneurial Collision Space.description: Hill Levene Entrepreneurial Collision Space is a bright, fun and flexible space is like no other on campus at University of Regina. The vision is to offer regular non-credit programming that will spark collaborative projects involving students from across campus

Saskatchewan Chamber Of Commerce.description: The Saskatchewan Chamber of Commerce represents the Saskatchewan business community, advocating on behalf of all sizes of businesses, local chambers of commerce, and professional associations.

SYPE.description: SYPE is a non-profit, membership-based organization of young professionals and entrepreneurs interested in meeting, learning, and connecting with each other.

StartupTNT.description: StartupTNT is a community of entrepreneurs, scientists, investors, innovators and startup supporters that gathers every week to have fun, share stories, and build great companies.

Cultivator.description: Cultivator powered by Conexus was built to create an innovation hub that provided the programming, resources, mentorship, funding, and space for founders to accelerate the growth of local tech startups.

Co.Labs.description: Co.Labs are passionate about growing Saskatchewan's tech ecosystem. Co.Labs is building a thriving tech ecosystem in Saskatchewan that will result in the emergence of new Series A startup(s) every year.

WESK.description: WESK a non-profit, membership-based organization of 800 members and growing, our main goal is to help you start, grow, and scale your business in Saskatchewan.

HackRegina.description: HackRegina is the beginning of a strong and well-known tech community for Regina, SK. The non-profit organization started as a small Slack channel but has ...

CSSS.description: CSSS - University of Regina Computer Science Students' Society, is a student driven socitey which helps students to grow and learn in the field of Computer Science.

URGDSC.description: GDSC is a university based community group presented by Google Developers. Students from all undergraduate and graduate programs with an interest to grow and thrive as a developer are welcome to join us.

IEEE.description: IEEE offers a number of ways to get involved with technical and local communities. These communities are active participants in research and authorship, conferences, and important conversations about today's most relevant technical topics locally and globally.

SaskGameDev.description: SaskGameDev is a community organization dedicated to promoting, enhancing and growing the game development industry in Saskatchewan.

URPATH.description: UR Path is designed to help you succeed both in and outside the classroom through experiential learning opportunities

URESS.description: University of Regina Engineering Students' Society

UMASS.description: University of Regina's Mathematics and Statistics Society

UR Ambassadors.description: The goals of Student Leadership Programs are to enhance the learning experience of our participants by providing them with interpersonal and leadership skill development opportunities, opportunities to create connections with other students and staff, and opportunities to give back to the university and the community.

CSEL.description: At the Centre for Experiential and Service Learning we're here to help you learn by doing, which is what experiential learning is all about! You’ll have more opportunities to apply what you learn – not only in the classroom, but across campus, and in the wider community.

Regina Open Door Society.description: The Regina Open Door Society (RODS) is a non-profit organization that provides settlement and integration services to refugees and immigrants in Regina.

Toastmasters.description: Toastmasters International is a nonprofit educational organization that teaches public speaking and leadership skills through a worldwide network of clubs.
